  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM). Across base airports: 14 high, 3 medium, 22 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT); plus 11 other bases. 3 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT). Network hotspots: Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Tromsø Airport, Langnes (TOS/ENTC), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Bodensee Airport Friedrichshafen (FDH/EDNY), Kaunas (KUN/EYKA) and 4 others. Primary drivers: mist, RVR limitations and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Tromsø Airport, Langnes (TOS/ENTC), Bodensee Airport Friedrichshafen (FDH/EDNY) and 9 others.",
